change.summary: Added a method to mark an execution as user / non-user into the AntTargetExecutor.Env

description.p: Added a method AntTargetExecutor.Env.setUserActionto mark an execution as user / non-user. The executions marked as user actions are registered in the UI support org.netbeans.spi.project.ui.support.BuildExecutionSupport. By default the execution is an user action.

change.summary: Added methods to override the default tab replacement policy into the AntTargetExecutor.Env

description.p: When the IDE is set to the automatic close tabs mode the tabs created by the previous run of the AntTargetExecutor are closed by successive run. Added a support to override this behavior.

change.summary: API for pinned Watches
change.description: A Watch.Pin base interface introduced as a basis for specific platform-dependent and location-dependent implementations. DebuggerManager.createPinnedwatch() introduced.

change.summary: Differentiate application-level exceptions
change.description: InvalidExpressionException can be thrown as a result of an application-level exception. We need to differentiate this case from exceptions thrown from NetBeans code. A boolean argument in the constructor and a method hasApplicationTarget() are added to InvalidExpressionException for this purpose.

change.summary: Enhanced smart-stepping.
change.description: SmartSteppingCallback.stopAt() method added to be able to override the default smart-stepping logic and provide specific steps that should be performed at given locations.

change.summary: CSS for Look and Feel
Added constants for module paths into the JavaClassPathConstants

description.p: Added constants for module paths into the JavaClassPathConstants.

change.summary: Added AccessibilityQueryImplementation2 to allow to listen on package accessibility changes

description.p: Added AccessibilityQueryImplementation2 interface and AccessibilityQuery.isPubliclyAccessible2 method to allow to listen on package accessibility changes.

change.summary: Added CompilerOptionsQuery for additional compiler options

description.p: Added CompilerOptionsQuery for passing additional compiler options to java infrastructure.

change.summary: Added a ClassPath switching among several ClassPath instances

description.p: Added a factory method into ClassPathSupport creating a ClassPath switching among several ClassPath instances.

change.summary: Support for decorating the creation process

description.p: In addition to provide CreateFromTemplateHandler which overtakes the template processing, CreateFromTemplateDecorator can participate in file creation doing pre- and post-creation tasks and edits either in the created file or other files.

change.summary: Maven Archetypes
change.description: One can now create project wizards that create new projects from Maven archetypes. See the how-to for more details.

change.summary: States for non-registered objects

description.p: When the scene is incrementally rendered, it may be possible that a model object becomes selected before some widgets are registered with the scene. Hover, select, focus flags can be attached even to unregistered objects.
Implemented in PR #308

change.summary: Can use classloader to check access to bootstrap classes

description.p: Bootstrap classloaders are not paired with a single module, yet they should obey visibility restrictions. The added method allows to check also accesses to resources served by bootstrap classloaders.
This change will hide classes (namely org.objectweb.asm, but also some core impl classes) that were visible in Apache NetBeans 9.0 release from NetBeans platform applications.

change.summary: PAC Script evaluation environment is now pluggable

description.p: The PAC Script Evaluation environment (as part of ProxySelector) has been completely rewritten and is now pluggable. (albeit for now only for friends)

change.summary: Introduced ModulePackages, ModuleMainClass, ModuleTarget attributes
change.description: Introduced ModulePackages, ModuleMainClass, ModuleTarget attributes according to recent JDK 9 JLS

change.summary: Updated ClassFile Module attribute to recent JDK 9 JLS
change.description: Updated ClassFile to recent JDK 9 JLS.

change.summary: Added isModule method into ClassFile
change.description: Added isModule method into a ClassFile to test that a classfile represents a module descriptor.

change.summary: Support for Java 9 Module attribute
change.description: Java 9 added a Module attribute for module-info.class describing the module.

change.summary: Show compact diff with netbeans.diff.default.compact system property
change.description: Added the system property netbeans.diff.default.compact which instructs the default DiffControllerProvider to show only the graphical diff (instead of the tabbed pane with the graphical and textual diffs).

change.summary: Added ordering for code template parameters.
Allow to protect existing text
change.description: Added method to create guarded block on top of existing text.

change.summary: Added category to EditorActionRegistration

description.p: Allow to set the keymap-category for an action registered using @EditorActionRegistration.

change.summary: Position.Bias support added to EditorCaret

description.p: CaretInfo.getDotBias() and CaretInfo.getMarkBias() added together with other methods and parameters for bias manipulation to properly handle bidirectional text.

change.summary: Renamed ShiftHighlightsSequence to SplitOffsetHighlightsSequence

description.p: Renamed ShiftHighlightsSequence to SplitOffsetHighlightsSequence to and its getStartShift() to getStartSplitOffset() for better description and getEndShift() to getEndSplitOffset().

change.summary: EditorUtilities.addCaretUndoableEdit added

description.p: EditorUtilities.addCaretUndoableEdit allows actions to remember caret position during an atomic transaction over a document.

change.summary: Support for sticky windows in the editor

description.p: Support for Sticky Windows in the editor. JComponents can be added to a layer on top of the editor. Components will update their vertical position on editor changes.

change.summary: Support for Navigation Filters, and caret move origins

description.p: Swing NavigationFilters implemented on top of the Caret API. Caret API caller may describe the operation which causes the caret to be moved, so that filters and caret listeners can react on specific action groups.
A boilerplate NavigationFilter is provided, that supports chaining of filters on the caret

change.summary: Added EditorRegistry.findComponent

description.p: The EditorRegistry.findComponent() allows caret related undo edits to be undone in a focused component (for multiple views over a single document).
Also simplified naming of EditorActionNames.addCaretUp and addCaretDown.

change.summary: Caret API introduced

description.p: The Caret API was introduced to allow working with multiple carets within one document.

change.summary: Extended HightlightsSequence by ShiftHighlightsSequence

description.p: Highlights sequence that supports shifts in addition to regular offsets. This allows to color individual spaces within a tab character or to color extra virtual characters beyond a newline character.

change.summary: Added IDs for goto prev/next occurrence actions

description.p: Many languages define their own actions and support for navigating between symbol occurrences. Common action name allows them to be presented and configured as one action in IDE configuration.

change.summary: Added support for adding weak property change listeners to documents

description.p: Added support for adding weak property change listeners to documents by providing DocumentUtilities.addWeakPropertyChangeListener(doc, listenerImplementation). The supplied listenerImplementation is not held via a strong reference, but a weak reference and so can be GCed independendly of the referencing document.

change.summary: Added methods to append elements to a GapList
change.description: Added supplementary methods to GapList to accompany the existing methods to add elements.

change.summary: Added factory method and interface to determine relationships between SourceGroups and modules

description.p: MultiModuleGroupQuery query interface allows to find out which module owns a particular SourceGroup. Project implementors can create an instance using new query method on QuerySupport.

change.summary: Added module-related properties to ProjectProperties

description.p: Added BUILD_TEST_MODULES_DIR to denote build location for tests in modular projects

change.summary: Platform combobox handles per project platforms

description.p: Platform combobox created by PlatformUiSupport handles per project JavaPlatforms.

change.summary: Boot ClassPath uses JavaPlatform defined in project

description.p: Boot ClassPath created by ClassPathProviderImpl uses a JavaPlatform defined in project.

change.summary: Added a factory method into QuerySupportto create a module-info based AccessibilityQueryImplementation2 instance

description.p: Added a factory method into QuerySupportto create a module-info based AccessibilityQueryImplementation2 instance.

change.summary: Added a factory method into QuerySupportto create unit tests CompilerOptionsQueryImplementation provider

description.p: Added a factory method into QuerySupportto create an implementation of the CompilerOptionsQueryImplementation providing explicit compiler options for tests compilation based on the source level and module-infos in source and test roots.

change.summary: Added a factory method into QuerySupportto createCompilerOptionsQueryImplementation provider

description.p: Added a factory method into QuerySupportto create an Ant property based implementation of the CompilerOptionsQueryImplementation.

change.summary: Added modulepath properties into the ProjectProperties

description.p: Added constants holding the modulepath property names into theProjectProperties. The following constants were added JAVAC_MODULEPATH, JAVAC_TEST_MODULEPATH, RUN_MODULEPATH,RUN_TEST_MODULEPATH, DEBUG_MODULEPATH,DEBUG_TEST_MODULEPATH.

change.summary: Assertion for missing fixes
change.description: A method assertFixesNotPresent was added to easily detect that fix is gone if e.g. some precondition is not met.

change.summary: Added a method to create default module properties
change.description: Added a method into the J2SEProjectBuilder to create default module properties for J2SEProject.

change.summary: Added a isValid method into JavaPlatform

description.p: Added a isValid method into JavaPlatform to check platform validity. The platform is non valid when it's deleted or an platform tool (java, javac) is missing or bootstrap libraries are missing.

change.summary: Added a SPI to create new JavaPlatform

description.p: Added a SPI allowing JavaPlatform implementors to export ability to create a new JavaPlatform.

change.summary: Added a SPI to manipulate with project's module-info.java declarations
change.description: Added a SPI interface, which should be implemented on project to provide backwards compatibility for ProjectClassPathModifier for modular projects.

change.summary: Added a LookupMerger for CompilerOptionsQueryImplementations
change.description: Added a factory method LookupMergerSupport.createCompilerOptionsQueryMerger to create a LookupMerger for CompilerOptionsQueryImplementations instances.

change.summary: Added a support for per project JavaPlatform

description.p: Added a support for per project JavaPlatform. The usecase for the per project JavaPlatform is a generated project. The project generator puts platform path into the project properties and the generated projects have correct JavaPlatform. There is no need to resolve broken JavaPlatform when the projects are opened.
To use the per project JavaPlatform set the platform.active property to the platform name and add the platforms.<platform_name>.home property pointing to the path to the JDK home.

Example:
platforms.MyJDK.home=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.7.0_67.jdk/Contents/Home
platform.active=MyJDK

change.summary: Extended the BrokenReferencesSupport.createPlatformVersionProblemProvider by the mininal source level supported by the project
change.description: Extended the BrokenReferencesSupport.createPlatformVersionProblemProvider by the mininal source level supported by the project

change.summary: Added a constant for execute module path into JavaRunner
change.description: Added a constant PROP_EXECUTE_MODULEPATH for execute module path into JavaRunner.

change.summary: Allows to extend the New Java File Wizard by project specific panels
change.description: Allows to extend the New Java File Wizard by project specific panels.

change.summary: Check the tree has compile error in given collection of errors.
change.description: Check the tree has compile error in given collection of errors.

change.summary: Check the tree is the end of compound declaration.
change.description: Check whether tree is part of compound declaration.

change.summary: Check the tree is the end of compound declaration.
change.description: Check the tree end with comma.

change.summary: Check the var type variable in given tree path.
change.description: Added BuildArtifactMapper.isCompileOnSaveSupported method, which checks if compile on save is suported in the current configuration.

change.summary: Check the var type variable in given tree path.
change.description: Check the var type variable in given tree path.

change.summary: Added a method to create an ElementHandle for module
change.description: Added a method to create a module ElementHandle from a module name.

change.summary: Added methods to generate/modify the module-info.java files
change.description: Added methods to generate/modify the module-info.java files

change.summary: Added an information about changes in the module-info
change.description: Added an information about changes in the module-info.

change.summary: List elements with their definining Scope
change.description: Allows to enumerate Elements matching passed ElementFilter according to hiding and inheritance rules. The method may be useful to list elements matching certain criteria, or to check whether an element exists and find what class/method defined it.

change.summary: Provide type suitable for declaration in source
change.description: Support method which allows to infer a type suitable for use in symbol declaration in the source was added.

change.summary: Allow to return also unimplemented default methods

description.p: findUnimplementedMethods and findOverridableMethods work better with interface default methods: they are treated as implemented, but overridable.
Allow ElementUtilities.findUnimplementedMethods enumerate also default methods whose implementations are not provided by class or superclasses.

change.summary: Code Generator uses caret location to insert members
change.description: Added an overloaded method to Code Generator should to include the caret location when inserting members. This will be used when the codestyle is CodeStyle.InsertionPoint.CARET_LOCATION.

change.summary: Adding ElementOpen.open(FileObject toSearch, TreePathHandle toOpen)
change.description: Adding ElementOpen.open(FileObject toSearch, TreePathHandle toOpen) method.

change.summary: Added a method to return an icon for module info directive
change.description: Added thegetModuleDirectiveIcon method into the ElementIcons to return an icon for a module info directive.

change.summary: NbModuleSuite.Configuration.parentClassLoader()

description.p: Adding a way to set parent classloader on which the NB platform should start.

change.summary: Support for source root grouping

description.p: A SourceRootConfig can be identifier by a structured "identifier" so when a new SourceGroup should be created as an associcate to existing sources, it is created in appropriate "sibling" location. See SourceGroupModifier for more details.

change.summary: Added a SourceGroupRelativeModifierImplementation to improve source root creation

description.p: In presence of multiple source roots, e.g. several source folders, or test folders, some of them may be more related to the

change.summary: Added a support method into ProjectConvertors creating a Lookup delegating to the owner project.

description.p: Added a support method into ProjectConvertors creating a Lookup delegating to the owner project.

change.summary: Command line with instances
change.description: Create command line with instances of OptionProcessor and ArgsProcessor.

change.summary: Print Usage into Caller's Stream
change.description: Env.usage method now takes an optional OutputStream parameter.

change.summary: Explictly specify option processors
change.description: CommandLine.html.create(Class...) can now be called with classes that extend OptionProcessor.

change.summary: Provide a way to have fixable annotation with default action
change.description: For custom type of annotations will dynamically register this annotation type as fixable, so Fix action (click on the icon) will work for it

change.summary: Support multiple ranges for ErrorDescriptor
change.description: Added support for multiple ranges for error/warning. New field added to ErrorDescription as well as corresponding getter method and new constructor in order to be able to provide multiple ranges support for highlight particular hint. Added new factory method to ErrorDescriptionFactory which uses new ErrorDescription constructor.

change.summary: Added JavaFixUtilities.isPrimary() utility

description.p: The utility method JavaFixUtilities.isPrimary() was added. This API checks whether a specified tree can be used in places where a Primary expression is required.

change.summary: Added SPI interface NavigatorPanel.DynamicRegistration

description.p: Added SPI interface NavigatorPanel.DynamicRegistration to allow dynamic registration of NavigatorPanels.

change.summary: Support model-based enabled and check state of actions

description.p: Context Actions which provide Action.SELECTED_KEY value will be presented as checkbox (menu) or toggle button (toolbar) and will reflect the state of an underlying model bean property, tracking models in Lookup and updating to model changes. Similar support was added for enabled Action property.
All that was required to be implemented by individual Actions in their ContextAwareAction implementations, this allows to use just annotation for the same behaviour in most cases.

change.summary: Separate template handling
change.description:
Now it's possible to register actions with
toggle property into Toolbar to get a toggle button.

change.summary: Introduces SortMode for natural sorting.

description.p: Added support for natural sorting of DataObjects. This means that the sort is case insensitive and number sequences are sorted by value rather than lexicographically.

change.summary: Adding ChildFactory.Detachable to allow ChildFactory implementations to attach and detach listeners more easily
change.description:
ChildFactory is useful for creating node children lazily on a background thread, and for simplifying working with Children.Keys. One oversight in the original API was providing for notification that the nodes created by the ChildFactory are no longer in use and should clean up any resources.
DestroyableNodesFactory is an abstract class which adds destroyNodes methods to ChildFactory.Detachable.

change.summary: BooleanStateAction deprecated in favour of Actions API and @ActionState annotation.

description.p: The BooleanStateAction base class was deprecated, as there's a programatic API in Actions and a declarative @ActionState annotation which fully supersede the deprecated class.

change.summary: API NetworkSettings.getAuthenticationPassword added

description.p: The SPI NetworkSettings.ProxyCredentialsProvider allows NetBeans Platform users to provide proxy and network credentials, but the according API should also provide the password, not only the username.

change.summary: Allow to select Mode for opening a TopComponent instance

description.p: Plugin implementors can direct to-be-opened TopComponents to appropriate Modes or prevent them to open in inappropriate Modes.
